&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Given&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp;K + P &amp;amp; M = S&amp;nbsp;:- K is the daughter of P, P is the wife of M, M is the father of S and&amp;nbsp;M has two daughters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/05/F3_Vinanti_SSC_02.05.23_D1_V2.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 112px; height: 106px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option (1): S is the cousin of K&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; &lt;strong&gt;False&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;[As S is the sister of K , thus S cannot the cousin of K as parent&amp;#39;s sibling&amp;#39;s children are called as cousin.]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option (2): S is the wife of K&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; &lt;strong&gt;False&lt;/strong&gt; [ As S is the sister of k, thus S cannot be the wife of K.]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option (3): S is the daughter in law of P&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; &lt;strong&gt;False&lt;/strong&gt; [ As S is the daughter of P , thus S cannot be the daughter-in-law of P and also P has only two daughters.]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Option (4): S is the sister of K&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; True&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; [As &amp;nbsp;S is the sister of K and daughter of M.&amp;nbsp;]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, &amp;quot;Option (4) : S is the sister of K&amp;quot; is the correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

